{
  "texts": [
    "Each neuron yields a positive neuron activation a ℓ i,j following the activation function if its inner product with x ℓ i is large.",
    "This activation subsequently scales w ℓ down.",
    "Therefore, an MLP output can be interpreted as a linear combination of the columns of W ℓ down, weighted by their respective neuron activations.",
    "To obtain human-understandable interpretation of individual MLP sub-update, we can project its value vector from the embedding space to the vocabulary space using the unembedding matrix W U and get an unnormalized distribution over all tokens (Hanna et al., 2024; nostalgebraist, 2020).",
    "This tells us the tokens it promotes when its corresponding neuron is activated (Geva et al., 2022)."
  ]
}